<!-- ===== ADVANCED FURNACES ===== -->

<h2 id="advanced-furnaces-en">Advanced Furnaces</h2>
<p>As you progress, you'll need higher heat furnaces for stronger metals.</p>

<h3 id="stone-furnace-en" style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px"><img src="/mite-be-wiki/img/blocks/furnace_stone_front.png" alt="" style="width:20px;image-rendering:pixelated;flex-shrink:0"> Stone Furnace</h3>
<p>8× Cobblestone. Max heat: 2. Used for glass, bricks, dyes and metal smelting — same heat level as Hardened Clay Furnace but <strong>more durable</strong>.</p>

<h3 id="obsidian-furnace-en" style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px"><img src="/mite-be-wiki/img/blocks/furnace_obsidian_front.png" alt="" style="width:20px;image-rendering:pixelated;flex-shrink:0"> Obsidian Furnace</h3>
<p>8× Obsidian. Max heat: <strong>3</strong>. The first furnace that can smelt <strong>Mithril ore</strong> (with lava bucket fuel).</p>

<h3 id="netherrack-furnace-en" style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px"><img src="/mite-be-wiki/img/blocks/netherrack_furnace_front.png" alt="" style="width:20px;image-rendering:pixelated;flex-shrink:0"> Netherrack Furnace</h3>
<p>8× Netherrack. Max heat: <strong>4</strong>. The only furnace that can smelt <strong>Adamantium ore</strong> — exclusively with Blaze Rod fuel!</p>
<div class="warning-box">🔥 <strong>Critical:</strong> Adamantium's melting point (6,210°C) exceeds the Obsidian Furnace maximum (5,000°C). <strong>Netherrack Furnace + Blaze Rod</strong> is the only way!</div>

<!-- ===== ORE PROCESSING ===== -->

<h2 id="ore-processing-en">Ore Processing</h2>
<p>Three methods to turn ore into ingots:</p>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Method</th><th>Process</th><th>Result</th><th>When Available?</th></tr>
  <tr><td>🧺 <strong>Sieving</strong></td><td>Sieve gravel → 9 ore fragments → furnace + mould</td><td>1 ingot</td><td>Early game (Hardened Clay Furnace)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>🔨 <strong>Hammer crushing</strong></td><td>Ore block + War Hammer → workbench</td><td>12 fragments → 1⅓ ingots</td><td>Bronze+ War Hammer required</td></tr>
  <tr><td>⛏️ <strong>Direct smelting</strong></td><td>Ore block → furnace</td><td>1 ingot</td><td>Appropriate furnace + fuel heat level</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="info-box"><strong>Tip:</strong> Hammer crushing extracts 33% more from an ore block than direct smelting (12 fragments → 1⅓ ingots vs. 1 ingot). You can also crush any metal ingot back into 9 ore fragments.</div>

<h3>War Hammer Requirements</h3>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Ore Block</th><th>Required Hammer</th><th>Output</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Copper / Silver / Gold</td><td>Bronze, Silver Copper, or High-Carbon Steel War Hammer</td><td>12 ore fragments</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Iron</td><td>High-Carbon Steel War Hammer only</td><td>12 ore fragments</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Any metal ingot</td><td>Any War Hammer (Bronze+)</td><td>9 ore fragments</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ===== CAMPFIRE ===== -->

<h2 id="campfire-en">Campfire</h2>
<div class="craft-section">
  <CraftingGrid recipeId="campfire" label={{hu: "Tábortűz", en: "Campfire"}}/>
</div>
<p>The campfire lets you cook meat <strong>properly</strong> — not burn it! Burned meat causes poisoning. Can cook <strong>8 pieces of meat</strong> at once.</p>
<div class="warning">Eating burned meat causes poisoning! Use a campfire!</div>
<div class="tip-card">🔥 <strong>Improvised grilling (without campfire):</strong> Drop raw meat on a flammable block (e.g., wood planks), then ignite with Flint and Steel. After the fire dies, light it again — about <strong>4 ignitions</strong> for full cooking.</div>

</div>

